snippet.textDisplay: I think that Osiris may be right. In the cutscene with him and Rasputin he called him a "betrayer". I think that we will power up Rasputin by the end of this season, but he will turn on us. He will allow the Almighty to crash into the last city and attack the survivors. That will lead to the next season being about us teaming up with everyone to defeat him. As the developers said in their shadowkeep dev stream, "season 11 will be unlike anything we have seen in Destiny before". This has never happened, (except to Lord Saladin and the Iron Lords), so this could be what they were talking about.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm hoping players of destiny will someday realize the reason why Zavala does so little is because his actions have so much impact.

Hence why this guardian is related to the story of Rasputin and Anna. Rasputin being a force of old but great power waiting to act. And Anna being a new influence wanting to do something but unknowing of the consequences.
